A SERIAL criminal held up terrified staff at a Glasgow bakery shop - and then boasted: Robber in boast after shop raid A SERIAL criminal held up terrified staff at a Glasgow bakery shop - and then boasted:&quot;It's as easy as that&quot;.Michael Lundie robbed the Greggs branch in Possilpark on May 18, pocketing more than &pound;300.The 27-year-old had brandished a large knife at two workers before storming behind the counter and demanding they open the till.Lundie was jailed for five years and three months yesterday after pleading guilty at the High Court in Glasgow to an assault and robbery charge. 